---
import ProseLayout from "../layouts/ProseLayout.astro";

export const prerender = true;
---

<ProseLayout
	title="CV"
	description="CV of Dr Fazeen Nasser — emergency medicine clinician, clinical AI builder, founding engineer."
>
	<div class="flex items-start justify-between flex-wrap gap-4 mb-8">
		<h1 class="mb-0">CV</h1>
		<a
			href="/Dr_Fazeen_Nasser_CV.pdf"
			target="_blank"
			class="meta text-accent hover:text-fg transition-colors inline-flex items-center gap-1.5"
		>
			Download PDF
			<svg width="13" height="13" viewBox="0 0 13 13" fill="none" aria-hidden="true">
				<path d="M6.5 1v7M3.5 5.5l3 3 3-3M1.5 10.5h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
			</svg>
		</a>
	</div>

	<h2>Professional Profile</h2>

	<p>
		Emergency medicine clinician at Barts Health NHS Trust (Whipps Cross Hospital) and founding engineer of clinical AI platforms Peerr.io and Aiigent.io. Seven years of experience building and deploying AI tools in healthcare settings, from early-stage prototypes to products used by hundreds of thousands of users. Particular focus on the implementation gap — the space between a working model and a deployed, evaluated, trusted clinical tool.
	</p>

	<h2>Current Clinical Post</h2>

	<p>
		<strong>ST3-equivalent Trust Grade Doctor — Emergency Medicine</strong><br />
		Whipps Cross Hospital, Barts Health NHS Trust, London<br />
		<span class="meta text-fg-subtle">November 2023 – present</span>
	</p>

	<p>
		Full-range undifferentiated emergency presentations across resus, majors, and ambulatory care. Co-lead of departmental QI project on mental health pathway compliance. Teaching of medical students and foundation doctors.
	</p>

	<h2>QI & Clinical Governance</h2>

	<p>
		<strong>Co-lead, Mental Health Pathway Compliance QIP</strong><br />
		Whipps Cross A&E, Barts Health NHS Trust<br />
		<span class="meta text-fg-subtle">2024 – present</span>
	</p>

	<p>
		Departmental quality improvement project auditing compliance with mental health pathways in the ED. Developed custom digital data-collection platform (qip.fazeen.dev) to replace paper-based audit forms. Data collection phase ongoing; departmental presentation and re-audit cycle planned.
	</p>

	<h2>Clinical AI & Healthcare Technology</h2>

	<p>
		<strong>Aide</strong> — AI-assisted clinical guideline retrieval for EDs · 2025–present<br />
		<strong>Peerr.io / Aiigent.io</strong> — Founding Engineer · 2023–present (15K+ users)<br />
		<strong>Leanifi</strong> — AI fitness and nutrition assistant · 2024–present<br />
		<strong>AskNICE</strong> — RAG interface over NICE guidelines · 2023<br />
		<strong>NeurallyMed</strong> — AI-powered PLAB exam prep, acquired 2023 · 2022–23<br />
		<strong>MIT COVID-19 Hackathon</strong> — Clinical AI triage, 2nd place · 2020<br />
		<strong>ET Tube Placement Detector</strong> — Deep learning, neonatal radiology · 2019<br />
		<strong>CXR Triage System</strong> — PyTorch CNN, chest X-ray prioritisation · 2018
	</p>

	<h2>Previous Clinical Experience</h2>

	<p>
		<strong>General Practitioner (Independent)</strong><br />
		Family practice, Kerala, India<br />
		<span class="meta text-fg-subtle">2022 – 2023</span>
	</p>

	<p>
		Sole clinician. Digitised a paper-based practice by partnering with a fintech-backed EHR startup — full installation, configuration, and staff onboarding.
	</p>

	<p>
		<strong>Medical Operations & Product Consultant</strong><br />
		DailyRounds / Marrow, Bengaluru, India<br />
		<span class="meta text-fg-subtle">December 2019 – June 2022</span>
	</p>

	<p>
		Medical lead at India's leading medical education platform. Led twenty medical editors across four specialty teams. Designed and launched the flagship "Pearls" feature. Primary clinical liaison between engineering and physician users. Scaled from early-stage to 500,000+ users.
	</p>

	<h2>Qualifications</h2>

	<p>
		<strong>MBBS</strong> — Kasturba Medical College, Manipal, India · 2019<br />
		<strong>GMC Registration</strong> — 7741002<br />
		<strong>ALS Provider</strong> — Resuscitation Council UK
	</p>

	<h2>Achievements</h2>

	<p>
		NHS England London InnovateMD 2026 Fellowship applicant (Digital & AI stream)<br />
		2nd place — MIT COVID-19 Hackathon, Clinical AI Track · 2020<br />
		NeurallyMed acquired · 2023
	</p>
</ProseLayout>
